GG_Resol_Gz5 Map Info

Size: small
Bots: Nav file included. 
Spawn Points: 12 for each side 
Discription: T and CT spawn in Different rooms which mirror each other each team runs forward ether up top or below into a central and open area. 
Creators Thoughts: When I made this map I was board and not trying.  Turns out that seems to work since this map was well liked by the server it was tested on.  It does have Hegrenade machines. 
Bugs: None I know of.

GG_Resol_Gz4 Map Info

Size: Medium 
Bots: Nav file included. 
Spawn Points: 12 for each side 
Discription: T and CT spawn in Different rooms which mirror each other and have 2 exits to get each other. The Rooms they start in are right on top of each other and as they exit the rooms can easy run into each other. 
Creators Thoughts: I Like this map as well.  Its easy to find the last bot and it seems to be hard to get to the Flash Nads,  which i was wanting since we dont want someone to camp them.  Even if they did camp it, its hard to use the nad and not be flashed your self. BUT the smoke nads CAN be spamed if theres few ppl left and there not careful :)
Bugs: None really other then the bots seem to ALL want to go the same way and they sometimes get stuck on each other.  Also not a big problem but u can hear foot steps from almost any ware.

GG_Resol_Gz3_1 Map Info

Size: Larger maybe even big 
Bots: Nav file included. 
Spawn Points: 12 for each side 
Discription: T and CT spawn in Different rooms which mirror each other and have 2 Hallways to get each other.  These hallways are large and long with both Flash and Granade. 
Creators Thoughts: I havent really tested this one with bots much.  I like the setup and the nad mechines but feel this map is just too big for a GG map.  Might make a good DM map.
Bugs: None I am aware of other then I could see people geting borad waiting for the last few players to find and kill each other, but that happens.

GG_Resol_Gz3 Map Info

  • Size: Large
  • Bots: Nav file included.
  • Spawn Points: 12 for each side
  • Discription: T and CT spawn in Different rooms which mirror each other and have 2 pathways out to get to a small connecting room which has a ladder to give access to the Upper and lower pathways.
  • Creators Thoughts: I Like playing this map with bots even thought they tend to be some what slow. 
  • Bugs: None unless you count the fact the center room is more of a oneway path even with the ladder and also I could see people geting borad waiting for the last few players to find and kill each other, but that happens.

This is Gz1 but Enlarged.  It is still on the small side but might be better suited for more players.
GG_Resol_Gz2 Map Info

  • Size: Small(ish)
  • Bots: Nav file included.
  • Spawn Points: 12 for each side (this map might work better then Gz1 with that many players
  • Discription: A central room with 3 levels and two entry points for each team.
  • Creators Thoughts: Nothing really since its Gz1 but wider.
  • Bugs: same as Gz1,  the entry locations for each team is easly seen from the other side.

This is basicly the first map I put together for CSS.
GG_Resol_Gz1 Map Info

  • Size: Small
  • Bots: Nav file included.
  • Spawn Points: 12 for each side (this map is to small for that many,  but then again I dont like lots of people on smaller maps)
  • Discription: A central room with 3 levels and two entry points for each team.
  • Creators Thoughts: Would work best with a small group of say 3v3 4v4 or so, any more then that and I personally would not like it.
  • Bugs: Only one I found when playing with bots and that was the two entry points for each team are visable for each team as they enter the central room so the bots tended to kill me before I even was able to enter the room.

This is a compacted version of the TF2 map.  It's extremely condensed as the 'forts' on either side are only facades more or less with steps in the back.  The spawn areas are in the water underneath the forts which can be quickly accessed via ladders.

The major difference between this and a lot of my other maps is that I made extensive use of func_detail brushes in order to speed up normal vis rendering (something that I should have learned long ago!) and making the maps run much faster in the end.  I'm learning other optimization techniques, so I will be attempting to make fast-running, yet detailed maps in the future.

This is the variant of gg\_realmaze\_a1. This map does not have the breakable boxes that gg\_realmaze\_a1 has, so it's a better map if your looking for a rounds game instead of gungame deathmatch. The map is a warehouse full of boxes that create an amazing tight and unpredictable labyrinth, making you feel like your lost but making you find your enemy at every corner! Be careful not to be humiliated while running!

Well, this is the first playable version of the map, I intend to add outside lightning trough windows, I plan on making the lamps to be breakable and I plan to give the map some optimization, even though it runs pretty well without it (I get 300 FPS with 9 bots in the game so...).

I hope you enjoy the map! Don't forget to comment and rate :)

This is a map that is very similar to my other gg\_200glockbullets map (That is based on the gg\_deagle\_assault), but this map is way much better than my first gg_200glockbullets. I decided to change the name instead of making it like a new version because I plan on changing a lot of things in the map and it wouldn't be correct because I was basically creating a new map, and also because it seems to me that the name of the map referring to GLOCK is getting people away from my map. 
This map has breakable boxes. When we get to the map, there are standard paths to walk, which by themselves make a good gaming situation, but when we break the boxes, we add several more paths to the map, adding complexity and fun to the game. The paths are completely different from any other map. One other feature, I made 4 types of boxes (in texture ways), there are the unbreakable boxes and three different breakable boxes with different textures and resistance. I also made boxes of different sizes, and the boxes maintain the same resistance value (example, a box has 5 of resistance, half of that box has only 2.5 of resistance).  
Well, this is the first playable version of the map, I intend to add outside lightning trough windows, I plan on making the lamps to be breakable and I plan to give the map some optimization, even though it runs pretty well without it (I get 300 FPS with 9 bots in the game so...).


I hope you enjoy the map! Don't forget to comment and rate :)
